Here's a fun and engaging way to write insertion sort in Java:

```java
public static void insertionSort(int[] arr) {
    for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
        int key = arr[i];
        int j = i - 1;
        while (j >= 0 && arr[j] > key) { // Swap elements if current element is greater than the key
            arr[j + 1] = arr[j]; // Move the greater element to the right
            j--; // Move to the previous index
        }
        arr[j + 1] = key; // Place the key in its correct position
    }
}
```

